he application process and completion of verification, financial assistance would be transferred to bank accounts of beneficiaries.Helpline for Delhi Driver Yojana by Transport Dept.In order to avail assistance on any issue related to Rs. 5,000 assistance under Delhi Driver Yojana, people can contact at the helpline number. All the auto, taxi, maxi cab drivers and owners of para transit vehicles can contact the helpline numbers at:- 011-23930763 011-23970290 Both these numbers are functional between 9 a.m. to 6 p.m except Sundays till 27th April 2020.Press Release of Corona Help Yojana by Delhi Transport Dept.Also check the press release by the state govt. for starting of online applications for Delhi Driver Yojana:-Delhi Driver Yojana Press Release Apply OnlineList of Documents to Apply Online for Delhi Driver SchemeBelow is the complete list of documents required to apply online for Delhi Driver Yojana 2020. In addition to the registration form, drivers must submit the necessary documents for consideration and acceptance of their applications. Any application must be filled by individual holder of PSV badge and valid DL of Para Transit Public Service Vehicles through online modules. The following information is required to be submitted:-Driving license numberPSV badge no.Mobile numberDate of birthGenderAadhaar numberOnly after submission of the completed application form along with these supporting documents, the apply online form would be considered.Eligibility for Delhi Driver Scheme 2020Read this section carefully in order to know who is eligible for the relief under Delhi Driver Yojana:-The beneficiaries of this scheme includes all owners of public transit passenger vehicles viz. Auto Rikshaw, Gramin Sewa, Taxis, Maxicab, Phatphat Sewa, e-Rikshaws, School cabs, Eco-Friendly Sewa etc.All the applicant drivers must be holding their valid driver\u2019s licence and PSV Badge.The assistance amount of Rs. 5,000 will be given to all the PSV Badge holders who have been issued these badges till 23rd March 2020 when the lockdown was started.If DL of any driver has been expired on or after 1st February 2020, they are also eligible and can apply for the benefit.Delhi Auto / Taxi / Cab Driver Yojana Assistance of Rs. 5,000In order to ensure that no person suffers from financial crunch, CM Kejriwal has decided to provide Rs. 5,000 to all the drivers. This includes owners of PSV badge holders as well as all valid DL holders.Delhi Driver Scheme 5000 CM Arvind KejriwalAll the drivers of auto rikshaws, taxis, phatphat sewa, e-rikshaws, maxi cab etc will be covered. The amount of Rs. 5000 will be transferred to the aadhaar linked bank accounts of the beneficiaries through the Direct Benefit Transfer (DBT) method. All the applicants are not required to visit in person at any govt. office to avail benefits. Application process is completely online. This is only one time financial assistance scheme.Timelines to Apply Online for Delhi Driver SchemeApplicants must remember the following dates to apply online for Delhi Driver Scheme in order to avoid any last time rush:- \u2014 Start Date of online registration \u2013 13 April 2020 \u2014 Last Date for online application \u2013 27 April 2020Official Announcement of Delhi Driver Yojana by CM KejriwalOn 12 April 2020, CM Kejriwal in his press conference has announced the Delhi Driver Scheme. The official tweet is here:-\u0926\u093f\u0932\u094d\u0932\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0911\u091f\u094b, \u0908-\u0930\u093f\u0915\u094d\u0936\u093e, \u0917\u094d\u0930\u093e\u092e\u0940\u0923 \u0938\u0947\u0935\u093e, \u092b\u091f-\u092b\u091f \u0938\u0947\u0935\u093e, \u091f\u0948\u0915\u094d\u0938\u0940 \u091a\u0932\u093e\u0928\u0947 \u0935\u093e\u0932\u0947 \u0939\u091c\u093e\u0930\u094b\u0902 \u0932\u094b\u0917 \u0932\u0949\u0915\u0921\u093e\u0909\u0928 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092c\u0947\u0930\u094b\u091c\u0917\u093e\u0930 \u0939\u094b \u0917\u090f \u0939\u0948\u0902\u0964 \u0909\u0928\u0915\u0947 \u092a\u093